
Overview of verb guard

The verb guard has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (6) guard -- (to keep watch over; "there would be men guarding the horses")
2. (6) guard, ward -- (watch over or shield from danger or harm; protect; "guard my possessions while I'm away")
3. (2) defend, guard, hold -- (protect against a challenge or attack; "Hold that position behind the trees!"; "Hold the bridge against the enemy's attacks")
4. guard -- (take precautions in order to avoid some unwanted consequence; "guard against becoming too friendly with the staff"; "guard against infection")

